    <div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-label">Reading time:</span> 12 min</div>
  </div>

  <div class="methodology">
    <p><strong>How this article was built:</strong> This investigation follows a structured editorial pipeline. Community discussions on Reddit, Trustpilot, and Quora were analysed to identify recurring questions and concerns. Regulatory sources (FTC guidance, legal analyses) were consulted for the legal framework. Independent third-party reviews were cross-referenced for factual data about OLSP's pricing and commission structure. Every factual claim in this article is labelled by source reliability.</p>
    <p><strong>Source reliability labels:</strong> <span class="rel-label verified">Verified</span> = independently verifiable from primary sources. <span class="rel-label vendor">Vendor Claim</span> = from OLSP's own marketing. <span class="rel-label third-party">Third-Party Reported</span> = from independent reviewers. <span class="rel-label self-reported">Self-Reported</span> = could not be independently verified. <span class="rel-label unverified">Unverified</span> = could not be confirmed at time of writing.</p>
